1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,360
Hello English learners.
各位英语学习者，大家好。

2
00:00:03,360 --> 00:00:04,640
Welcome back to EnglishPod.
欢迎回到EnglishPod。

3
00:00:04,640 --> 00:00:05,840
My name is Marco.
我是Marco。

4
00:00:05,840 --> 00:00:07,120
And I'm Erica.
我是Erica。

5
00:00:07,120 --> 00:00:09,760
And today we're going to be taking you to the airport.
今天我们要带你去机场。

6
00:00:09,760 --> 00:00:10,760
That's right.
没错。

7
00:00:10,760 --> 00:00:17,120
We're going to listen as a man checks in at the airport and deals with his luggage.
我们会听一位男士在机场办理登机手续和处理行李的过程。

8
00:00:17,120 --> 00:00:18,120
That's right.
没错。

9
00:00:18,120 --> 00:00:20,780
So we're going to be looking at a lot of great stuff that can help you the next time you
所以我们会看到很多很棒的内容，能帮到你下次

10
00:00:20,780 --> 00:00:24,040
are at the airport at the check-in counter.
在机场值机柜台时。

11
00:00:24,040 --> 00:00:28,480
So why don't we take a look at one word that we're going to preview today in Vocabulary
那我们不如先看看今天在“词汇预览”中要预览的一个词。

12
00:00:28,480 --> 00:00:30,600
Preview.
词汇预览。

13
00:00:30,600 --> 00:00:32,540
Vocabulary Preview.
词汇预览。

14
00:00:32,540 --> 00:00:36,480
We're going to hear this guy say, I'd like to check three pieces.
我们会听到这个人说：“我想托运三件。”

15
00:00:36,480 --> 00:00:39,800
He's going to check three pieces of what?
他要托运三件什么？

16
00:00:39,800 --> 00:00:41,660
Pieces of luggage.
三件行李。

17
00:00:41,660 --> 00:00:45,560
So when we talk about luggage, we can say pieces of luggage.
所以当我们谈论行李时，可以说“pieces of luggage”。

18
00:00:45,560 --> 00:00:46,560
That's right.
没错。

19
00:00:46,560 --> 00:00:48,940
Luggage is a non-count noun.
“Luggage”是不可数名词。

20
00:00:48,940 --> 00:00:52,180
So you can't say one luggage, two luggages, three luggages.
所以你不能说“one luggage”、“two luggages”、“three luggages”。

21
00:00:52,180 --> 00:00:53,180
That's wrong.
那是错的。

22
00:00:53,180 --> 00:00:54,180
Right.
对。

23
00:00:54,180 --> 00:00:56,480
So we use pieces of luggage.
所以我们用“pieces of luggage”。

24
00:00:56,480 --> 00:00:57,480
Okay.
好的。

25
00:00:57,480 --> 00:01:00,080
He's going to check three pieces of luggage.
他要托运三件行李。

26
00:01:00,080 --> 00:01:01,080
Very good.
很好。

27
00:01:01,080 --> 00:01:02,840
Let's listen to our dialogue for the first time.
让我们第一次听对话。

28
00:01:02,840 --> 00:01:07,720
We're going to see what happens with this guy at the airport and with his pieces of
我们会看看这个人在机场和他的行李发生了什么。

29
00:01:07,720 --> 00:01:17,480
luggage.
行李。

30
00:01:17,480 --> 00:01:18,480
Next please.
下一位。

31
00:01:18,480 --> 00:01:19,600
Hello, sir.
您好，先生。

32
00:01:19,600 --> 00:01:21,480
May I see your passport, please?
请出示您的护照好吗？

33
00:01:21,480 --> 00:01:22,480
Yes.
好的。

34
00:01:22,480 --> 00:01:23,480
Here you go.
给你。

35
00:01:23,480 --> 00:01:25,040
Will you be checking any bags today?
今天要托运任何行李吗？

36
00:01:25,040 --> 00:01:26,040
Yes.
是的。

37
00:01:26,040 --> 00:01:27,520
I'd like to check three pieces.
我想托运三件。

38
00:01:27,520 --> 00:01:29,120
I'm sorry, sir.
对不起，先生。

39
00:01:29,120 --> 00:01:34,640
Airline policy only allows two pieces of checked luggage at 20 kilograms each plus one piece
航空公司政策只允许托运两件行李，每件20公斤，外加一件

40
00:01:34,640 --> 00:01:36,160
of carry-on luggage.
随身行李。

41
00:01:36,160 --> 00:01:38,800
I will have to charge you extra for the additional suitcase.
您需要为额外的行李箱支付费用。

42
00:01:38,800 --> 00:01:39,800
What?
什么？

43
00:01:39,800 --> 00:01:40,800
Why?
为什么？

44
00:01:40,800 --> 00:01:41,920
I'm taking an intercontinental flight.
我坐的是洲际航班。

45
00:01:41,920 --> 00:01:44,320
I'm flying 16,000 kilometers.
我要飞16,000公里。

46
00:01:44,320 --> 00:01:47,520
How am I supposed to take only two 20 kilo bags?
我怎么可能只带两个20公斤的包？

47
00:01:47,520 --> 00:01:48,520
That's absurd.
这太荒谬了。

48
00:01:48,520 --> 00:01:49,760
I'm sorry, sir.
对不起，先生。

49
00:01:49,760 --> 00:01:51,240
There's nothing I can do.
我无能为力。

50
00:01:51,240 --> 00:01:54,400
You cannot board the flight with that large bag either.
您也不能带着那个大包登机。

51
00:01:54,400 --> 00:01:58,400
Carry-on bags must fit in the overhead compartment or under your seat.
随身行李必须能放进头顶行李架或座位下面。

52
00:01:58,400 --> 00:02:00,760
That bag is clearly too big.
那个包明显太大了。

53
00:02:00,760 --> 00:02:01,760
Now I see.
现在我明白了。

54
00:02:01,760 --> 00:02:03,640
You charge next to nothing for an international ticket.
国际机票你们几乎不收费。

55
00:02:03,640 --> 00:02:07,880
When it comes to charging for any other small thing, you charge an arm and a leg.
但一提到其他小东西收费，你们就狮子大开口。

56
00:02:07,880 --> 00:02:11,920
So tell me, miss, how much will I have to pay for all of this?
所以告诉我，小姐，所有这些我要付多少钱？

57
00:02:11,920 --> 00:02:12,920
Let's see.
让我看看。

58
00:02:12,920 --> 00:02:13,920
$625 US dollars.
625美元。

59
00:02:13,920 --> 00:02:25,200
That's more than my round-trip ticket!
那比我的往返机票还贵！

60
00:02:25,200 --> 00:02:28,000
All right, well, that's a whole lot of money, isn't it?
好吧，那可真是一大笔钱，对吧？

61
00:02:28,000 --> 00:02:30,560
Well, I think it's a very common situation.
嗯，我觉得这是很常见的情况。

62
00:02:30,560 --> 00:02:34,680
I'm sure many of our listeners can relate to this situation.
我相信很多听众都能感同身受。

63
00:02:34,680 --> 00:02:37,480
Overweight charges are pretty expensive.
超重费相当贵。

64
00:02:37,480 --> 00:02:38,480
Very high.
非常高。

65
00:02:38,480 --> 00:02:40,000
I know from personal experience.
我亲身经历过。

66
00:02:40,000 --> 00:02:41,500
But that's not what we want to talk about now.
但这不是我们现在要谈的。

67
00:02:41,500 --> 00:02:48,280
We want to talk about some really useful vocabulary in Language Takeaway.
我们想在“语言精华”中讨论一些非常有用的词汇。

68
00:02:48,280 --> 00:02:49,280
Language Takeaway.
语言精华。

69
00:02:49,280 --> 00:02:53,960
All right, on Language Takeaway today, we have five words.
好的，今天的“语言精华”里，我们有五个词。

70
00:02:53,960 --> 00:02:55,880
So why don't we start with the first one?
那我们不如从第一个开始？

71
00:02:55,880 --> 00:03:00,000
So the woman asked, will you be checking any bags today?
所以那位女士问：“今天要托运任何行李吗？”

72
00:03:00,000 --> 00:03:02,680
Will you be checking any bags today?
今天要托运任何行李吗？

73
00:03:02,680 --> 00:03:04,000
To check bags.
托运行李。

74
00:03:04,000 --> 00:03:05,000
Right.
对。

75
00:03:05,000 --> 00:03:06,840
So the verb to check.
所以动词“to check”。

76
00:03:06,840 --> 00:03:12,720
It means to give your bags to the airline, to register them.
意思是把你的行李交给航空公司，进行登记。

77
00:03:12,720 --> 00:03:15,280
Okay, so that's what happens with your luggage.
好的，这就是你的行李的处理方式。

78
00:03:15,280 --> 00:03:18,960
You check them, so basically they become responsible for your bags.
你托运它们，基本上他们就对你的行李负责了。

79
00:03:18,960 --> 00:03:19,960
Right.
对。

80
00:03:19,960 --> 00:03:22,680
It reminds me of checking in to a hotel.
这让我想起入住酒店。

81
00:03:22,680 --> 00:03:23,880
Right, very similar.
对，很相似。

82
00:03:23,880 --> 00:03:26,600
When you go to a hotel, you register at the hotel.
你去酒店时，在酒店登记。

83
00:03:26,600 --> 00:03:28,120
You check in.
你办理入住。

84
00:03:28,120 --> 00:03:30,480
In this case, you just check your luggage.
在这种情况下，你只是托运你的行李。

85
00:03:30,480 --> 00:03:31,640
You don't check in your luggage.
你不是办理行李入住。

86
00:03:31,640 --> 00:03:32,640
Right.
对。

87
00:03:32,640 --> 00:03:34,400
Okay, so check luggage.
好的，所以是“check luggage”。

88
00:03:34,400 --> 00:03:40,400
So he wanted to check three pieces of luggage, and he also had carry-on luggage.
所以他想要托运三件行李，他还有随身行李。

89
00:03:40,400 --> 00:03:41,840
Carry-on luggage.
随身行李。

90
00:03:41,840 --> 00:03:43,200
Carry-on.
随身携带的。

91
00:03:43,200 --> 00:03:45,600
So carry-on luggage, it's pretty simple.
“Carry-on luggage”很简单。

92
00:03:45,600 --> 00:03:47,680
That's right, you carry it on yourself.
没错，你自己随身携带。

93
00:03:47,680 --> 00:03:50,320
Exactly, you carry it on to the plane.
对，你把它带上飞机。

94
00:03:50,320 --> 00:03:54,200
Now we can talk about carry-on luggage, right?
现在我们可以说“carry-on luggage”，对吧？

95
00:03:54,200 --> 00:03:55,680
Or carry-on bag.
或者“carry-on bag”。

96
00:03:55,680 --> 00:03:57,960
Right, or a carry-on suitcase.
对，或者“carry-on suitcase”。

97
00:03:57,960 --> 00:04:00,640
A very small suitcase that can fit under your seat.
一个很小的行李箱，能放在座位下面。

98
00:04:00,640 --> 00:04:01,640
Exactly.
没错。

99
00:04:01,640 --> 00:04:03,560
All right, so carry-on luggage.
好的，所以是“carry-on luggage”。

100
00:04:03,560 --> 00:04:08,520
Now he was traveling on an intercontinental flight.
他当时乘坐的是洲际航班。

101
00:04:08,520 --> 00:04:10,280
Intercontinental.
洲际的。

102
00:04:10,280 --> 00:04:11,600
Intercontinental.
洲际的。

103
00:04:11,600 --> 00:04:13,600
We have two words there, inter.
这个词有两部分，“inter”。

104
00:04:13,600 --> 00:04:14,600
Between.
在……之间。

105
00:04:14,600 --> 00:04:15,600
Between, right?
在……之间，对吧？

106
00:04:15,600 --> 00:04:16,600
And continental.
和“continental”。

107
00:04:16,600 --> 00:04:18,160
So this sounds like continent.
所以听起来像“continent”（大陆）。

108
00:04:18,160 --> 00:04:24,640
Okay, so he's traveling maybe from Asia to North America.
好的，所以他可能从亚洲飞到北美。

109
00:04:24,640 --> 00:04:26,640
Okay, intercontinental.
好的，洲际的。

110
00:04:26,640 --> 00:04:30,320
He's trying to board this intercontinental flight.
他试图登上这趟洲际航班。

111
00:04:30,320 --> 00:04:32,880
So to board a flight.
所以是“board a flight”。

112
00:04:32,880 --> 00:04:34,400
Board a plane.
登机。

113
00:04:34,400 --> 00:04:35,400
Board a train.
上火车。

114
00:04:35,400 --> 00:04:37,600
All right, so basically it means to...
好的，所以基本上意思是……

115
00:04:37,600 --> 00:04:38,600
To get on.
上（交通工具）。

116
00:04:38,600 --> 00:04:39,600
To get on.
上（交通工具）。

117
00:04:39,600 --> 00:04:40,600
To get on a vehicle.
上交通工具。

118
00:04:40,600 --> 00:04:44,360
Okay, so I can say board the ship, board the car.
好的，所以可以说“board the ship”、“board the car”。

119
00:04:44,360 --> 00:04:45,360
No.
不行。

120
00:04:45,360 --> 00:04:46,360
No?
不行？

121
00:04:46,360 --> 00:04:47,360
No.
不行。

122
00:04:47,360 --> 00:04:48,360
But board the train.
但可以说“board the train”。

123
00:04:48,360 --> 00:04:49,360
Board the train.
上火车。

124
00:04:49,360 --> 00:04:50,360
Board the bus.
上公交车。

125
00:04:50,360 --> 00:04:51,960
All aboard.
全体上车。

126
00:04:51,960 --> 00:04:55,560
That's right, that's why in movies you see that somebody will yell all aboard.
没错，这就是为什么在电影里你会看到有人喊“全体上车”。

127
00:04:55,560 --> 00:04:56,560
Yeah.
嗯。

128
00:04:56,560 --> 00:04:57,560
In the train station, right?
在火车站，对吧？

129
00:04:57,560 --> 00:04:58,560
Exactly.
没错。

130
00:04:58,560 --> 00:04:59,560
All aboard.
全体上车。

131
00:04:59,560 --> 00:05:06,440
Okay, so board a vehicle and our last phrase for today, overhead compartment.
好的，所以是“board a vehicle”，我们今天的最后一个短语是“overhead compartment”。

132
00:05:06,440 --> 00:05:08,480
Overhead compartment.
头顶行李架。

133
00:05:08,480 --> 00:05:09,480
Overhead compartment.
头顶行李架。

134
00:05:09,480 --> 00:05:13,160
All right, let's break this phrase down.
好的，我们来分解这个短语。

135
00:05:13,160 --> 00:05:14,400
Overhead.
“Overhead”。

136
00:05:14,400 --> 00:05:16,840
So that's on top of your head, right?
所以是在你头顶上方，对吧？

137
00:05:16,840 --> 00:05:17,840
Exactly.
没错。

138
00:05:17,840 --> 00:05:18,840
Above you.
在你上面。

139
00:05:18,840 --> 00:05:24,120
Yeah, and the compartment is a place where you can put something and store it.
嗯，“compartment”是一个可以放东西并储存的地方。

140
00:05:24,120 --> 00:05:25,120
Kind of like a box.
有点像盒子。

141
00:05:25,120 --> 00:05:26,120
Right.
对。

142
00:05:26,120 --> 00:05:27,120
Yeah.
嗯。

143
00:05:27,120 --> 00:05:31,880
So overhead compartment, that big box where you put your bags and your purse or whatever
所以“overhead compartment”，就是飞机上那个大箱子，你放包、钱包或其他东西的地方。

144
00:05:31,880 --> 00:05:32,880
on an airplane.
嗯。

145
00:05:32,880 --> 00:05:33,880
Mm-hmm.
嗯。

146
00:05:33,880 --> 00:05:36,160
Very similar to, for example, an overhead projector.
和“overhead projector”很像。

147
00:05:36,160 --> 00:05:41,000
Right, so that's the machine that puts an image or a picture on a wall, like sometimes
对，那是一种把图像或图片投射到墙上的机器，比如有时在会议上能看到。

148
00:05:41,000 --> 00:05:42,280
you see them in meetings.
对，因为图像在你头顶上方而且很大，所以叫“overhead projector”。

149
00:05:42,280 --> 00:05:46,840
Right, so because the image is over your head and it's big, it's called an overhead projector.
好的，所以是一些很棒的语言。

150
00:05:46,840 --> 00:05:49,160
Okay, so some great language.
好的，所以是一些很棒的语言。

151
00:05:49,160 --> 00:05:54,520
Why don't we hear it again in context by listening to the dialogue for the second time?
我们不如再听一遍对话，在上下文中感受一下？

152
00:05:54,520 --> 00:05:58,000
Next, please.
下一位。

153
00:05:58,000 --> 00:06:00,960
Hello, sir.
您好，先生。

154
00:06:00,960 --> 00:06:05,960
May I see your passport, please?
请出示您的护照好吗？

155
00:06:05,960 --> 00:06:08,440
Yes, here you go.
好的，给你。

156
00:06:08,440 --> 00:06:10,880
Will you be checking any bags today?
今天要托运任何行李吗？

157
00:06:10,880 --> 00:06:14,960
Yes, I'd like to check three pieces.
是的，我想托运三件。

158
00:06:14,960 --> 00:06:16,880
I'm sorry, sir.
对不起，先生。

159
00:06:16,880 --> 00:06:23,920
Airline policy allows only two pieces of checked luggage at 20 kilograms each, plus one piece
航空公司政策只允许托运两件行李，每件20公斤，外加一件

160
00:06:23,920 --> 00:06:25,720
of carry-on luggage.
随身行李。

161
00:06:25,720 --> 00:06:29,880
I will have to charge you extra for the additional suitcase.
您需要为额外的行李箱支付费用。

162
00:06:29,880 --> 00:06:30,880
What?
什么？

163
00:06:30,880 --> 00:06:31,880
Why?
为什么？

164
00:06:31,880 --> 00:06:35,080
I'm taking an intercontinental flight.
我坐的是洲际航班。

165
00:06:35,080 --> 00:06:38,280
I'm flying 16,000 kilometers.
我要飞16,000公里。

166
00:06:38,280 --> 00:06:42,160
How am I supposed to take only two 20-kilo bags?
我怎么可能只带两个20公斤的包？

167
00:06:42,160 --> 00:06:43,160
That's absurd.
这太荒谬了。

168
00:06:43,160 --> 00:06:45,000
I'm sorry, sir.
对不起，先生。

169
00:06:45,000 --> 00:06:47,040
There's nothing I can do.
我无能为力。

170
00:06:47,040 --> 00:06:50,960
You cannot board the flight with that large bag either.
您也不能带着那个大包登机。

171
00:06:50,960 --> 00:06:56,080
Carry-on bags must fit in the overhead compartment or under your seat.
随身行李必须能放进头顶行李架或座位下面。

172
00:06:56,080 --> 00:06:58,680
That bag is clearly too big.
那个包明显太大了。

173
00:06:58,680 --> 00:07:00,200
Now I see.
现在我明白了。

174
00:07:00,200 --> 00:07:04,860
You charge next to nothing for an international ticket.
国际机票你们几乎不收费。

175
00:07:04,860 --> 00:07:11,080
But when it comes to charging for any other small thing, you charge an arm and a leg.
但一提到其他小东西收费，你们就狮子大开口。

176
00:07:11,080 --> 00:07:16,200
So tell me, miss, how much will I have to pay for all this?
所以告诉我，小姐，所有这些我要付多少钱？

177
00:07:16,200 --> 00:07:17,200
Let's see.
让我看看。

178
00:07:17,200 --> 00:07:18,200
$625 US dollars.
625美元。

179
00:07:18,200 --> 00:07:19,200
No.
不。

180
00:07:19,200 --> 00:07:23,440
That's more than my round-trip ticket.
那比我的往返机票还贵。

181
00:07:23,440 --> 00:07:25,360
All right.
好吧。

182
00:07:25,360 --> 00:07:31,080
So I think it's a little bit more clear now.
所以我觉得现在更清楚一些了。

183
